Note: Only works on operating systems supported by Drake (Ubuntu 22.04, Ubuntu 24.04)

Ensure that Drake is installed globally and is on PATH
Ensure that ros2-humble is installed and has been sourced
	$source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash

1. Create a workspace directory and a src directory inside
2. Clone this repository into the src directory
	$git clone https://github.com/xandermaljaars/high_level_robot_controller.git
3. Clone the other required packages that need to be built.
	$git clone https://github.com/RobotLocomotion/drake-ros.git
4. Navigate to the workspace directory and use rosdep to install all required packages
	$rosdep install --from-paths src -ryi
5. Navigate back to the workspace directory and build the project
	$colcon build
6. Source the workspace installation
	$source install/local_setup.bash
7. (TODO) Run the controller using the "" launch script
	$ros2 launch controller ""
	Use the simulation:=true to start the simulation but omit it if the actual robot is on and ready to run
